Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:32.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.67,0:16:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nanako!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.26,0:16:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. She isn't able to talk a lot yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.27,0:16:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dojima, you came here again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.73,0:16:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.52,0:16:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that you're worried about your daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.06,0:16:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you still need your rest, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.52,0:16:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.07,0:16:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I'll wheel him back to his room immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What do you think you're doing, Adachi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.36,0:16:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dojima, that's so lame!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.78,0:17:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.70,0:17:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.66,0:17:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.76,0:17:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Namatame...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still mentally unstable,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but we're slowly piecing together his story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.93,0:17:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything new?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.43,0:17:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this is still a secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.89,0:17:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I guess it's okay to tell you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were entries about Ms. Yamano and Ms. Konishi in the diary we found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.28,0:17:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Namatame had been making advances on Ms. Konishi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We think that could be connected to why he killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.83,0:17:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.54,0:17:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, I'm gonna go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanamura...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry! I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.17,0:17:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bottle it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.17,0:17:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.59,0:17:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Namatame's been caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.05,0:18:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't hurt anyone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.93,0:18:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.56,0:18:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When do you think Nanako can go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.73,0:18:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dojima's still hospitalized, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.36,0:18:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I wonder what's up with this fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.29,0:18:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know a person whose child has been bedridden because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it's really poisonous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.20,0:18:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run! Evacuate immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is poisonous gas! It's loaded with viruses!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll die if you breathe this fog!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.91,0:18:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with him? What a creep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.42,0:18:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The idea that this fog is poisonous is just plain stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although that was an extreme example,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wouldn't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.04,0:18:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.38,0:18:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that people are getting increasingly worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.92,0:18:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.34,0:18:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People everywhere are talking about the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's very unusual for fog to last this long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Visibility's so bad, it's kinda scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.73,0:18:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean in the TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.81,0:18:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Guys, put on your glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.69,0:18:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, it's all clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.32,0:18:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.61,0:19:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the hell's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These glasses are meant to help us see through the fog in the other world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But putting that aside, no glasses would improve one's visibility in a fog under normal circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.29,0:19:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could the fog from over there be leaking into our world?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.04,0:19:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You guys think that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.25,0:19:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It just popped into my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could the fog from the TV world really be leaking into our world?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.63,0:19:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.14,0:19:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.64,0:19:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.23,0:19:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does seem a lot like the fog on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.86,0:19:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but beyond that, I'm clueless.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.03,0:19:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the case against Namatame hasn't been going well, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.99,0:19:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.08,0:19:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Adachi,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.74,0:19:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they haven't made any progress with Namatame's interrogations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems he's still confined to his hospital bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.21,0:19:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so further interrogation has yet to commence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.09,0:20:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fog isn't leaving, and the interrogation isn't going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.30,0:20:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We solved the case, but I still feel bummed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.30,0:20:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.18,0:20:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I still stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.27,0:20:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What brought that on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.19,0:20:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You kept your promise to help me find the person who was disrupting the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.24,0:20:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I guess we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I should be going back,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.78,0:20:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't wanna go until Nana gets better.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.29,0:20:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do we have to say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.21,0:20:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you can stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.79,0:20:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Master, are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.13,0:20:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really mean it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.59,0:20:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.09,0:20:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe I should move in with you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.76,0:20:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being together would really heat things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.55,0:20:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, it {\i1}has{\i0} been unusually cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.98,0:20:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you promised Nanako?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.40,0:21:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I promised that we'd go buy a space heater.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.07,0:21:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're getting a space heater, we'd better get some oranges to complete the set.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.45,0:21:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.70,0:21:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanji, what'd you buy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.45,0:21:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.29,0:21:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that wool?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.25,0:21:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Nanako and I could make some knitted animals when she gets better,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.71,0:21:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they're for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanji, you're so sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.30,0:21:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screw you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.51,0:21:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While we're all here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why don't we pick out a Christmas present for Nanako?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.19,0:21:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The space heater isn't good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.48,0:21:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.65,0:21:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, as soon as Nanako's out of the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.53,0:21:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how about we have a party at your place?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.53,0:21:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A party? That sounds nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.91,0:21:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! And we'll bake the cake!
